T1  - An ex ante analysis of put-call parity
AU  - Klemkosky, Robert C.
AU  - Resnick, Bruce G.
JO  - Journal of Financial Economics
VL  - 8
IS  - 4
SP  - 363
EP  - 378
PY  - 1980
DA  - 1980/12/01/
SN  - 0304-405X
DO  - https://doi.org/10.1016/0304-405X(80)90008-2
UR  - https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/0304405X80900082
AB  - The authors previously had extended the theoretical put-call parity models developed by Stoll (1969) and Merton (1973) to include a dividend term. Ex post tests of the models were generally consistent with market efficiency, but a sufficient number of hedges had high enough returns to warrant analysis of ex ante results. The purpose of this study was to construct hedges 5 and 15 minutes after they were initially identified as having an ex post return in excess of $20 per hedge. The results indicate that mispriced options adjust and that economic profit is sensitive to the level of transaction costs and unlikely even for member firms.
ER  - 
